{"metadata":{"externalID":"c:@M@OUDSTokensSemantic@objc(cs)MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","roleHeading":"Class","symbolKind":"class","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"OUDSTokensSemantic"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens"}],"title":"MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens"}]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["        \/\/ Assuming in Figma with have a font semantic token typeDisplayLarge,","        \/\/ with values depending to size class. These values are defined as font composite raw tokens.","        let typeBold850 = FontCompositeRawToken(size: fontSize850, lineHeight: fontLineHeight1050, weight: fontWeight700, letterSpacing: fontLetterSpacing850)","        let typeBold1450 = FontCompositeRawToken(size: fontSize1450, lineHeight: fontLineHeight1850, weight: fontWeight700, letterSpacing: fontLetterSpacing1450)","","        \/\/ Then the develoment team declares an \"higher\" level font semantic token","        \/\/ inside FontCompositeSemanticTokens protocol,","        \/\/ and defined inside OUDSTheme+FontCompositeSemanticTokens extension","        var typeDisplayLarge: MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens {","            MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens(compact: FontRawTokens.typeBold850, regular: FontRawTokens.typeBold1450)","        }","","        \/\/ If the same font is used whatever the size class is","        var typeDisplayLarge: MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens { MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens(FontRawTokens.typeBold650) }","","        \/\/ The theme exposes both generated elevation semantic tokens and \"crafted\" higher level elevation semantic tokens.","        \/\/ It is recommended to use the higher level version as it is less error-prone."],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The case of this "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens"},{"type":"text","text":" is quite particular because in fact it contains "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FontCompositeRawToken"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(i.e. raw tokens) instead of semantic tokens."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In fact there is not “font composite semantic tokens” defined in the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figma","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" kit."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","name":"Since","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0.8.0"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/multiplefontcompositerawtokens"]}],"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Kind of semantic tokens which will wrap a combination of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FontCompositeRawToken"},{"type":"text","text":" depending to size classes."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Kind of composite token with multiple values, but not named “composite” because this word is already used in the design system."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Allows to gather the multiple-value tokens fr